Packages & Imports

Key Points:
* packages nest like inner classes
* chaining x.y.z leaves intermediate packages x and x.y invisible
* package objects can hold functions and variables
* imports can be anywhere and rename/hide members
* java.lang, scala, and Predef are always imported

Importing allows shorter names

import java.awt._

def handler(evt: event.ActionEvent) // java.awt.event.ActionEvent

Renaming members
import java.util.{HashMap => JavaHashMap}
import scala.collection.mutable._

Importing multiple members
import java.awt.{Color, Font}
